Three-dimensional sonographic diagnosis of abdominal wall endometriosis: a useful tool? To report the usefulness of three-dimensional (3D) ultrasonography for the assessment of parietal endometriosis.Case report.Academic research hospital.A 35-year-old woman with a noncyclic, painful abdominal nodule near a caesarean delivery scar.3D ultrasonography and wide surgical resection with healthy margins.3D ultrasonographic assessment of the endometriotic nodule.We found that 3D ultrasonography offered a more specific description of parietal endometriosis with irregular and spiculated margins and depth infiltration as well as provided preoperative evaluation of volume measurements.Three-dimensional ultrasonography is a useful, noninvasive tool in extrapelvic endometriosis.